        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="KR4h0001-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-5a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-13T23:22:17.541+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:02:16.799+09:00">Kong Rong [153-208],</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:02:16.83+09:00">The literary men of this day are</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:02:21.284+09:00">Chen Lin [d. 217], called Kongzhang, of Kuang-ling;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:02:52.48+09:00">Wang Can [177-217], called Zhongxuan, of Shangyang;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:03:21.039+09:00">Xu Gan [170-217], called Weichang, of Peihai;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:04:06.676+09:00">Ruan Yu [ca 165-212], called Yuanyu, of Chenliu;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:04:26.63+09:00">Ying Chang [d. 217], called Delian, of Runan;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:04:58.359+09:00">and Liu Zhen [d. 217], called Gonggan, of Dongping.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:05:26.574+09:00">These seven masters</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T20:01:04.994+09:00">have omitted nothing in their learning,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:05:47.072+09:00">have no borrowed collors in their diction.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:06:13.308+09:00">Yet they have found it most difficult to all gallop together a thousand leagues,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T20:09:38.16+09:00">side by side with equal pace on their mighty steeds,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:06:55.077+09:00">and thus to pay one another due respect.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T20:16:33.096+09:00">A superior person examines himself to measure others;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:08:27.563+09:00">and thus he is able to avoid such entanglements [e.g. envy and blindness to the worth of others].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-7a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:08:46.69+09:00">Thus I have written a discourse on literature.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:09:36.66+09:00">Wang Can excels in poetic expositions;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:09:52.475+09:00">even though Xu Gan at times shows languid qi,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:10:15.879+09:00">still he is Wang Can's match.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T21:37:10.12+09:00"> works like "Beginning of the Journey," "Climbing a Tower," "The Locust Tree," or "Thoughts on Travel"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:12:41.807+09:00">or works like Xu Gan's "The Black Gibbon," "The Syphon," "The Circular Fan," or "The Orange Tree."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:15:09.596+09:00">Yet their other writings</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:15:11.748+09:00">are no match for these.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:15:23.815+09:00">In regard to memorials, letters and records</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:15:38.551+09:00">those of Chen Lin and Ruan Yu are preeminent in the present.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:16:03.244+09:00">Ying Chang is agreeable but lacks vigor.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:16:35.24+09:00">Liu Chen is vigorous but holds nothing concealed [mi; i.e. in reserve].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:16:50.551+09:00">Kong Rong's form and qi are lofty an subtle</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:17:05.802+09:00">with something in them that surpasses all the others;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:17:42.641+09:00">but he cannot sustain an argument,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:17:37.753+09:00">and the principle in his work is not up to the diction.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:18:07.559+09:00">to the point that he mixes his writing with playfulness and spoofing.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:18:18.609+09:00">At his best</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T22:25:22.704+09:00">he rivals Yang Xiong [53BC-AD. 18] and Ban Gu.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-9a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:20:49.109+09:00">Ordinary people value what is far away and feel contempt for what is close at hand.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-9a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:21:01.922+09:00">They favor repute and turn their backs on substance.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-9a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T23:50:57.704+09:00">Moreover, the suffer the ill consequences of ignorance in self-awareness,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-9a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:21:31.283+09:00">claiming to be men of great worth.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-9a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:35:39.801+09:00">Literature</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-9a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:36:27.864+09:00">is the same at the root, but differs in its branches [mo, a "branch tip," the later stages of a process].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-9a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:37:00.626+09:00">Generally speaking, memorials and disquisitions should have dignity;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-9a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:37:23.259+09:00">letters and memorials should be based on natural principle;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-9a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:37:37.083+09:00">inscriptions and eulogy value the facts;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-9a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:37:59.415+09:00">poetry and poetic exposition aspire to beauty.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-9a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:38:15.892+09:00">Each of these four categories is different,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-9a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:38:27.905+09:00">so that a writer's ability will favor some over others.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-9a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:38:58.697+09:00">Only a comprehensive talent can achieve the full complement of these forms.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-10a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:39:49.443+09:00">In literature qi is the dominant factor.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-10a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-15T02:11:52.737+09:00">Qi has its normative forms - clear and murky. [For the expression the tonalities of qi there is style.???CH]</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-10a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:40:16.324+09:00">It is not to be brought by force.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-10a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:40:27.271+09:00">Compare it to music:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-10a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:50:05.69+09:00">though melodies be equal</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-10a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:50:04.764+09:00">and though the rhythms follow the rules,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-10a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:41:05.874+09:00">when it comes to an inequality in drawing on a reserve of qi,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-10a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:41:28.328+09:00">we have grounds to distinguish skill and clumsiness.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-10a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:41:38.548+09:00">Although it may reside in a rather,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-10a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:42:14.28+09:00">he cannot transfer it to his son; nor can an elder brother transfer it to the younger.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:45:46.287+09:00">I would say that literary works are the supreme achievement in the business of state,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:45:53.224+09:00">a splendor that does not decay.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:46:09.453+09:00">A time will come when a person's  life ends</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-15T03:52:58.036+09:00">glory and pleasure go no further than this body.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:46:37.499+09:00">To carry both to eternity,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:46:58.864+09:00">there is nothing to compare with the unending permanence of the literary work.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:47:43.818+09:00">So writers of ancient times</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-15T03:58:44.849+09:00">entrusted their persons to ink and the brush</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-15T17:25:15.243+09:00">and let their thoughts be seen in their compositions;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-15T17:27:57.604+09:00">depending neither on a good historian</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:48:56.729+09:00">nor on momentum from a powerful patron,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:49:17.614+09:00">their reputations were handed down to posterity on their own force.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:51:17.19+09:00">The Earl of the West [later made King Wen of the Zhou], when imprisoned, amplified the Book of Changes;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:52:02.076+09:00">the Duke of Zhou, though in his glory, prescribed the Rites.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:52:38.129+09:00">The former did not ignore this [the importance of literary work] in spite of hardship;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:52:46.417+09:00">the latter was not distracted by health and pleasure.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:53:02.285+09:00">From this we can see</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:53:57.244+09:00">how the ancients thought nothing of large jade disks [marks of wealth], but valued each moment,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-15T21:09:17.501+09:00">fearful lest their time pass them [read 己CH] by.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:54:29.123+09:00">Yet people usually do not exert themselves:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:54:42.389+09:00">in poverty and low station they fear the hunger and cold;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:54:55.955+09:00">amid wealth and honour they drift with the distractions of pleasure.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:55:31.838+09:00">They busy themselves with the demands of what lies right before their eyes,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:55:44.493+09:00">and neglect an accomplishment lasting a thousand years.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:56:02.616+09:00">Overhead, the days and months pass away from us;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:56:16.356+09:00">here below, face and body waste away.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:56:41.258+09:00">Suddenly we will move off into transformation with all the other things of the world-</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:56:54.347+09:00">this is the greatest pain for a person with high aspirations.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:57:11.207+09:00">Kong Rong and the others have already passed away,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-15T21:44:01.955+09:00">and only the discourses composed by Xu Gan</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-11a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T00:57:59.871+09:00">are the fully realized work of an individual writer.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-6a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T19:03:42.67+09:00">writing in a letter to his elder brother Ban Zhao [33-108]:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-6a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T19:04:04.373+09:00">"Wuzhong [Fu Yi] became Imperal Librarian through his facility in composition:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-6a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T19:04:22.799+09:00">whenever he used his writing brush, he couldn't stop himself."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-6a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T19:41:05.538+09:00">People are good at [or fond of] making themselves known;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-6a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T19:04:55.966+09:00">but since literature is not of one form along</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-6a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T19:05:11.101+09:00">few can be good at everything.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-6a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T19:05:26.831+09:00">Thus each person disparages that in which he is weak</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-6a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T19:05:37.676+09:00">by the criterion of those things in which he is strong.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-6a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T19:05:47.194+09:00">There is a village saying:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-6a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T19:06:03.571+09:00">"The worn-out broom that belongs to my household</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-6a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T19:57:51.573+09:00">is worth a thousand in gold."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-6a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T19:58:43.511+09:00">Such is the ill consequence of a lack of self-awareness.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_052-8a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-14T21:37:48.042+09:00">Even Zhang Heng [78-139] and Cai Yong [132-192] do not surpass</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-17T20:52:46.77+09:00">At break of day my heart is still unquiet,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-17T20:53:01.759+09:00">I dress myself, then stand there hesitating.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-18T00:09:12.961+09:00">I hesitate, not knowing where I should go -</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-17T20:53:24.793+09:00">A recluse may dwell in a secluded valley.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-17T20:53:37.865+09:00">In the morning he culls crss in the suthern gorge,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-17T20:53:55.711+09:00">At night he rests at the foot of the western hill.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-17T20:54:09.507+09:00">Light branches lace above him like the clouds,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-17T20:54:35.322+09:00">Thick foliage forms a tent of kingfisher-green.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-17T20:54:52.091+09:00">Eddying winds linger in the grove of magnolias,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-17T20:55:07.591+09:00">Their fragrance swirls to meet the graceful trees.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-17T21:10:49.085+09:00">The pleasant plashing of the mountain burn (!)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-17T20:56:01.549+09:00">Mournful music wells from these magic waters,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-18T01:52:31.165+09:00">Their mournful echoes echo in the coigns of the crags</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-18T00:41:19.327+09:00">Their falling notes echo in coigns of the crags,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-18T00:41:38.546+09:00">Such perfect joy can simply not be feigned,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-17T21:24:31.859+09:00">Why harm the Primal Unity with meddling?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-17T22:48:20.623+09:00">If wealth and renown are difficult to obtain,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR4h0001_tls_022-3a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-12-17T22:48:04.983+09:00">better halt my carriage and do what I want to do.</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
